CatDescriptText: Miss Evelyn Trinclisti, salesgirl, Apollo and Mr. J.M. Williams, salesman, Philadelphia, were part of the Pittsburghers Speak Up column published in the Pittsburgh Courier Newspaper, March 3, 1962, pg. 10 with question: "In what way do you think the successful orbiting of Col. John Glenn will aid the United States in its relationship with other countries?"  Ms. Trinclisti's answer reads: "I imagine it will help by giving people more confidence in the United States.  Also, I think it will help us in dealing with Russia."  Mr. Williams' answer reads: "I don't think it will build our prestige too much.  The competition is too keen - there are so many countries involved in this business."
TitMainTitle: Two frames: Portrait of Evelyn Trinclisti wearing dark unbuttoned overcoat, standing in front of ribbed metal wall; Portrait of J.M. Williams wearing wool hat, sweater, and light colored overcoat, standing in front of ribbed metal wall
